# Jinja2 Template Development Standards

Apply these conventions when generating or modifying Jinja2 templates.

---

## Template header

Every template must begin with a comment describing its purpose and expected variables:

```jinja2
{#
  Template: VS Code Extensions Configuration
  Output:   .vscode/extensions.json
  Required: extensions (list[str])
  Optional: debug_mode (bool, default false)
#}
```

---

## Indentation and formatting

- Use 2-space indentation for template logic
- Place Jinja2 block tags on their own lines when they contain multi-line content
- Use trailing commas in all JSON array templates — eliminates conditional comma logic

```jinja2
{# ✅ Good: trailing commas, consistent indentation #}
{
  "recommendations": [
{% for ext in extensions %}
    "{{ ext }}",
{% endfor %}
  ]
}

{# ❌ Bad: conditional comma logic is error-prone #}
{% for ext in extensions %}
    "{{ ext }}"{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
```

---

## Variable safety

Always provide defaults for optional variables. Never access a variable without a guard when it may be undefined:

```jinja2
{# Safe access #}
{{ config.description | default("Auto-generated configuration") }}

{# Conditional rendering #}
{% if deployment_platform is defined and deployment_platform %}
"deploymentPlatform": "{{ deployment_platform }}",
{% endif %}

{# Safe list operations #}
{% set extensions = config.extensions | default([]) %}
{% for ext in extensions %}
    "{{ ext }}",
{% endfor %}
```

---

## Type filters

Use proper Jinja2 filters to handle data types in JSON/YAML output:

```jinja2
{# Strings — escape with tojson #}
"description": {{ task.description | tojson }},

{# Booleans — lowercase #}
"enabled": {{ config.enabled | lower }},

{# Numbers — explicit cast #}
"port": {{ config.port | int }},

{# JSON objects — tojson for inline serialisation #}
"settings": {{ config.settings | tojson }},
```

---

## Reusable macros

Define macros for patterns used more than once:

```jinja2
{% macro extension_list(items) %}
[
{% for item in items %}
  "{{ item }}",
{% endfor %}
]
{% endmacro %}

"required":    {{ extension_list(config.required_extensions) }},
"recommended": {{ extension_list(config.recommended_extensions) }},
```

---

## Security

- **Never** pass user-controlled input directly into template logic
- Sanitise file path variables to prevent traversal:

```jinja2
{# Safe path — strip traversal sequences #}
"configPath": "{{ config_path | replace('..', '') | trim }}",
```

- Use `{{ value | tojson }}` for any string originating from user input to ensure proper JSON escaping
- Do not use `eval` or dynamic template path loading with user-supplied values

---

## Null and error handling

```jinja2
{# Null-safe array rendering #}
{% if config and config.extensions %}
"extensions": [
{% for ext in config.extensions %}
  "{{ ext }}",
{% endfor %}
]
{% else %}
"extensions": []
{% endif %}

{# Type guard before iteration #}
{% if config.tasks is iterable and config.tasks is not string %}
{% for task in config.tasks %}
    {# process task #}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
```

---

## Pre-calculation pattern

Cache expensive or repeated computations outside loops:

```jinja2
{# Pre-calculate once, reuse throughout #}
{% set has_python  = 'python' in languages %}
{% set has_testing = config.testing_framework is defined %}
{% set filtered    = languages | selectattr('enabled') | list %}

{% if has_python and has_testing %}
  {# Python testing configuration #}
{% endif %}
```

---

## Quality checklist

Before committing a template:

- [ ] Header comment documents output file, required, and optional variables
- [ ] All arrays use trailing commas (not `{% if not loop.last %}`)
- [ ] All optional variables have `| default(...)` fallbacks
- [ ] All user-derived strings pass through `| tojson` or `| replace`
- [ ] Generated output is valid JSON/YAML after rendering
- [ ] Tested with empty input, single-element, and multi-element collections
